{"commentSequence": 17783084, "userLocation": "Philadelphia", "userTitle": "NULL", "parentID": null, "sharing": 0, "userDisplayName": "Brice C. Showell", "status": "approved", "userURL": "NULL", "commentBody": "Destroying a cell phone is more like the act of a terrorist than a football player.", "createDate": "1457102151", "recommendations": 3, "updateDate": "1457110948", "commentTitle": "<br/>", "userID": 34185878, "picURL": "https://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/apps/timespeople/none.png", "depth": 1, "replies": [{"commentSequence": 17786334, "userLocation": "excramento", "userTitle": "NULL", "parentID": 17783084, "sharing": 0, "userDisplayName": "cfb cfb", "status": "approved", "userURL": "NULL", "commentBody": "It was broken, he was buying a new one, and its a very common practice for celebrities to destroy their old phones so they don't end up in the hands of the paparazzi.<br/><br/>Not to mention the league had everything they needed from it and told Brady that it was okay to destroy it.<br/><br/>Lets not let pesky facts get in the way of a good lynching though.", "createDate": "1457113925", "recommendations": 8, "updateDate": "1457118730", "commentTitle": "<br/>", "userID": 60581931, "picURL": "https://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/apps/timespeople/none.png", "depth": 2, "replies": [], "permID": "17783084:17786334", "recommendedFlag": null, "timespeople": 1, "reportAbuseFlag": null, "approveDate": "1457118730", "trusted": 0, "commentType": "userReply", "parentUserDisplayName": "Brice C. Showell", "commentID": 17786334, "replyCount": 0, "editorsSelection": false}, {"commentSequence": 17787906, "userLocation": "West Coast", "userTitle": "NULL", "parentID": 17783084, "sharing": 0, "userDisplayName": "DougP", "status": "approved", "userURL": "NULL", "commentBody": "Cfb cfb, it is unfathomable that Brady's lawyers would allow him to destroy that phone. Any competent lawyer should have been able to predict how that would look. Doesn't matter if it was broken or whatever. Either his lawyers were grossly incompetent or Brady decided it was more advantageous to get rid of the phone. There is no third option.", "createDate": "1457125652", "recommendations": 4, "updateDate": "1457125745", "commentTitle": "n/a", "userID": 55943269, "picURL": "https://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/apps/timespeople/none.png", "depth": 2, "replies": [], "permID": "17783084:17787906", "recommendedFlag": null, "timespeople": 1, "reportAbuseFlag": null, "approveDate": "1457125745", "trusted": 0, "commentType": "userReply", "parentUserDisplayName": "Brice C. Showell", "commentID": 17787906, "replyCount": 0, "editorsSelection": false}, {"commentSequence": 17788129, "userLocation": "NY, NY", "userTitle": "NULL", "parentID": 17783084, "sharing": 0, "userDisplayName": "Matt Ng", "status": "approved", "userURL": "NULL", "commentBody": "And the NFL has proven to be a leak free organization?  Sure, I'd shred my phone if I were Brady, especially when Wells said it was no longer needed.", "createDate": "1457127752", "recommendations": 1, "updateDate": "1457129091", "commentTitle": "<br/>", "userID": 65468241, "picURL": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/pimage.timespeople.nytimes.com/6546/8241/cropped-65468241.jpg?0.7182554090421214", "depth": 2, "replies": [], "permID": "17783084:17788129", "recommendedFlag": null, "timespeople": 1, "reportAbuseFlag": null, "approveDate": "1457129091", "trusted": 0, "commentType": "userReply", "parentUserDisplayName": "Brice C. Showell", "commentID": 17788129, "replyCount": 0, "editorsSelection": false}], "permID": "17783084", "recommendedFlag": null, "timespeople": 1, "reportAbuseFlag": null, "approveDate": "1457110948", "trusted": 0, "commentType": "comment", "parentUserDisplayName": null, "commentID": 17783084, "replyCount": 3, "editorsSelection": false}